## When to use
Use this skill when you need to analyze and monitor CPU usage on a multi-core or multi-processor Linux system.

## Approach
To monitor CPU usage, utilize the `shell_exec` tool to run the `mpstat` command. The mpstat command provides statistics for each processor in the system, allowing detailed analysis of individual CPUs.

## Example
```bash
# Use shell_exec to execute mpstat every second for 10 seconds and capture the output.
output=$(shell_exec "for i in {1..10}; do echo -n '.'; mpstat 1 1 | grep 'All\|Linux' ; done")
echo "$output"
```

## Pitfalls
- Ensure that `mpstat` is installed on your system before running this command.
- Monitor the output carefully as high-frequency polling can impact system performance.